Title : German Society of Surgery
Text : [[File:German Society of Surgery.png|thumb|Logo.]]{{Primary sources|date=March 2018}}
The '''German Society of Surgery''' ({{lang-de|Deutsche Gesellschaft für Chirurgie}}) is a German medical organization.

It was founded in 1872 and is one of the oldest medical-scientific [[learned societies]]. It is headquartered in [[Berlin]] and is headed by president Joachim Jähne and secretary-general Hans-Joachim Meyer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dgch.de/index.php?id=118|title=Welcome to the website of the German Society of Surgery (DGCH)|publisher=German Society of Surgery|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

